r, 'Wife-Swapping in Medieval Literature'. The references and bibliography have been updated, and a new preface surveys publications in the field over the last decade. JILL MANN is currently Notre Dame Professor of English, University of Notre Dame.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism and literaturexHistoryyTo 1500zEngland. 0aWomen and literaturexHistoryyTo 1500zEngland. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 500-1500zEngland. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChaucer's thinking.  aFemale virtues.  aFeminist criticism.  aGender roles.  aLiterary analysis.  aMasculinity.  aMedieval literature.  aMisogynist stereotypes.  aPower roles.  aWife-swapping.  aWomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846150722?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846150722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846150722/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles